.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.SINCE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.since \- Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.since()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]since()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R]
instances returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing
the duration from another date (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.from()\f[R]) to this date.
The duration is positive if the other date is before this date, and
negative if after.
.PP
This method does \f[CR]this \- other\f[R].
To do \f[CR]other \- this\f[R], use the \f[CR]until()\f[R] method.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
since(other)
since(other, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]other\f[R]
A string, an object, or a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instance
representing a date to subtract from this date.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object using the same
algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.from()\f[R].
It must have the same calendar as \f[CR]this\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object containing the options for
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration.prototype.round()\f[R], which includes
\f[CR]largestUnit\f[R], \f[CR]roundingIncrement\f[R],
\f[CR]roundingMode\f[R], and \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R].
\f[CR]largestUnit\f[R] and \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R] only accept the
units: \f[CR]\(dqyears\(dq\f[R], \f[CR]\(dqmonths\(dq\f[R],
\f[CR]\(dqweeks\(dq\f[R], \f[CR]\(dqdays\(dq\f[R], or their singular
forms.
For \f[CR]largestUnit\f[R], the default value \f[CR]\(dqauto\(dq\f[R]
means \f[CR]\(dqdays\(dq\f[R] or \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R], whichever is
greater.
For \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R], the default value is
\f[CR]\(dqdays\(dq\f[R].
The current date is used as the \f[CR]relativeTo\f[R] option.
Note that using units larger than \f[CR]\(dqdays\(dq\f[R] may make the
duration not portable to other calendars or dates.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing the duration
\f[I]since\f[R] \f[CR]other\f[R] to this date.
The duration is positive if \f[CR]other\f[R] is before this date, and
negative if after.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]other\f[R] has a different calendar than \f[CR]this\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Any of the options is invalid.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using since()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2022\-12\-25\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] now = Temporal.Now.plainDateISO();
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = now.since(date);
\f[B]const\f[R] formatter = \f[B]new\f[R] Intl.DurationFormat(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { style: \(dqlong\(dq });
console.log(\(gaIt\(aqs been ${formatter.format(duration)} since that Christmas...\(ga);
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqIt\(aqs been [number] days since that Christmas...\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] duration2 = now.since(date, { smallestUnit: \(dqmonths\(dq });
console.log(\(gaIt\(aqs been ${formatter.format(duration2)} since that Christmas...\(ga);
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqIt\(aqs been [number] months since that Christmas...\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] duration3 = now.since(date, {
  largestUnit: \(dqyears\(dq,
  smallestUnit: \(dqmonths\(dq,
});
console.log(\(gaIt\(aqs been ${formatter.format(duration3)} since that Christmas...\(ga);
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqIt\(aqs been [number] years, [number] months since that Christmas...\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Rounding the result
By default the fractional part of the \f[CR]smallestUnit\f[R] is
truncated.
You can round it up using the \f[CR]roundingIncrement\f[R] and
\f[CR]roundingMode\f[R] options.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date1 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2022\-01\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2022\-01\-28\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = date2.since(date1, {
  smallestUnit: \(dqdays\(dq,
  roundingIncrement: 5,
  roundingMode: \(dqceil\(dq,
});
console.log(duration.toString()); \f[I]// \(dqP30D\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SS Comparing different calendars
By default, the two dates must have the same calendar.
This is to avoid ambiguity in the meaning of months and years.
If you want to compare dates from different calendars, you can convert
them to the same calendar first.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date1 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2022\-01\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2022\-01\-28[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = date2.withCalendar(\(dqiso8601\(dq).since(date1);
console.log(duration.toString()); \f[I]// \(dqP27D\(dq\f[R]
.EE
